ympics\">given a place in the singles</a> draw following the withdrawal of Croatia's Petra Martic.</li> <li>The Russian gold medal favourite Oksana Slivenko has been <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-oksana-silvenko-weightlifting\">forced to withdraw from the women's 69kg weightlifting</a> because of injury.</li> <li>The <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-queen-olympic-cauldron\">odds against the Queen lightening the Olympic cauldron</a> have been slashed following a flurry of late bets.</li> <li>The <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-5012934095cb5fcda7f95206\">mayor of Liverpool</a> and <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-tweet-greeks-cowardly-fake\">German hockey player Neither Keller</a> have been involved in Twitter-based imbroglios.</li> </ul> <p>Xan Brooks is<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-opening-ceremony-live\"> liveblogging the opening ceremony here</a>, and will guide you through the remainder of the evening. Enjoy!</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012d05b95cb5fcda7f9523c\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery picture gallery</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Fans of sports photography should be rubbing their hands with glee. Here's <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/gallery/2012/jul/27/olympics-2012-olympics-2012-archery\">the best of the pictures of this morning's women's archery</a>. Any doubts about quite how big the Olympics are should be dispelled by this one: this is how many journalists cover the so-obscure-it's-not-even-on-the-telly women's archery ranking round.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-4ad02916-b0f7-419b-9576-300333a05e35\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343410144661/90f550e8-84aa-42ed-bb3c-5ee4eab4a26e-460.jpeg\" alt=\"Scores of journalists work at Lord's during the archery.\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>The press centre at Lord's during the women's archery ranking round.</figcaption> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012cccc95cb5fcda7f9523b\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Michael Phelps</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>And Andy Bull <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/michael-phelps-missy-franklin-london-21012\">has written about Michael Phelps</a>, whose final Olympics starts tomorrow, when he'll go in at the deep end with his first head-to-head battle against Ryan Lochte. \"These are the last competitive moments that I will have in my career,\" he said. \"It's big. There are going to be a lot of firsts and a lot of lasts this week. I won't be holding back when I am in the pool.\"</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012cb78b579c24ed04374e4\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Phillips Idowu</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>UK Athletics' chief executive, Niels de Vos, has insisted that Phillips Idowu will be fit in time for the Games despite insiders at the governing body confirming that they have no new information on the triple jumper's state of health, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/phillips-idowu-fitness-london-2012\">reports An</a><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/phillips-idowu-fitness-london-2012\">na Kessel</a>. A hip injury to one of the most likely gold-medalists in Britain's athletics team has <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/23/london-2012-olympics-phillips-idowu\">caused great concern</a>, but today De Vos told Sky Sports News: \"I'm very confident Phillips will be fit. He's a very experienced athlete, he's preparing in the best way he sees and if he's ready, which I believe he will be, I think he'll do very well &ndash; it's as simple as that.\"</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012c9fb95cb5fcda7f95235\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Cauldron-lighting latest</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Following news from earlier today that the Queen was being heavily backed to light the Olympic cauldron at the opening ceremony, it's now being suggested that as many as seven people could be involved in the moment of ignition, among them Roger Bannister.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012c934b579c24ed04374de\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Greenwich latest</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Stephen Moss is <em>still</em> walking the route of the equestrian cross-country.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>There are some very amusing details. Models of sheep and squirrels. Lovely big butterfly. Real veg on the East End Barrows. Nice bit where the horses have to enter the arena to jump a model of the Tower of London. A wharf near the river where they jump a model of a barge. A farm where they jump a trailer pulled by a tractor. Horses have to do this in 10 mins. I've been walking for an hour and a half and am knackered. Soldier just stopped me to check identity. Said there were reports of intruder in the park.<br /><br /></p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012c82295cb5fcda7f95232\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Full report on this morning's archery action</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Eddie Butler, who was allowed to watch events unfold at Lord's, has filed <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-south-koreans-archery\">his report on this morning's men's archery</a>, which was dominated by the record-breaking South Koreans. Im Dong-hyun, who is legally blind, scored 699 out of a possible 720.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012c76195cb5fcda7f95230\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">BBC rivals allowed six minutes of Olympic footage a day</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Elsewhere on The Guardian, John Plunkett has written about fact that, while the BBC will broadcast 2,500 hours of live Olympic footage over the Olympics, its <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/2012/jul/27/bbc-rivals-six-minutes-olympics-footage\">commercial rivals will be limited to just six minutes' coverage a day</a> &ndash; split over no more than three news bulletins, each containing no more than two minutes of Olympic footage, and containing no more than a third of any individual event (though the 100m can be shown in full).</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012c665b579c24ed04374da\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bradley Wiggins previews the road race</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Bradley Wiggins' <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/blog/2012/jul/27/bradley-wiggins-mark-cavendish-london-2012\">latest Guardian column</a> looks ahead to tomorrow's road race, where Britain's Mark Cavendish is the favourite.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>This is what Cav has been living for for most of the year. The road race title is what he's been thinking about since he won the world's last September. He looks as fit as I've ever seen him. I told him I think black makes him look fat, but he looks different now he's wearing Great Britain blue. He's been rallying the troops, telling us what a fantastic team we are, and how he has no doubt we will be around him in the finale. It's probably the strongest team ever in an Olympic road race. We're all humble about what we have achieved but externally we must look like the dominant force.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012c04595cb5fcda7f9522d\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">President Obama says...</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/BarackObama/status/228880151025442817\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>U.S.A.! U.S.A.! <a href=\"http://t.co/p5Jvz59J\" title=\"http://twitter.com/BarackObama/status/228880151025442817/photo/1\">twitter.com/BarackObama/st…</a></p>&mdash; Barack Obama (@BarackObama) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/BarackObama/status/228880151025442817\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T15:50:55+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012bfea95cb5fcda7f9522c\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Sudanese embassy: asylum-seeking athlete story untrue</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Sudanese embassy has released a statement addressing the <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-5012b088b579c24ed04374ce\">reports</a> that a member of their team has applied for political asylum.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We herewith categorically refute allegations in some newspapers and news agencies that a Sudanese member of those who qualified for the Olympic competition and have arrived in London is either missing sought political asylum. <br /> <br />We take this opportunity to salute the London 2012 Olympic Games Organizing Committee for the thorough preparations and hope that our athletes will justify their selection and compete fairly and honourably in this great city of London. The whole delegation will no doubt return with the best of memories and new friendships. <br /><br /></p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012bedcb579c24ed04374d6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>    <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>So, what does it feel like to win an Olympic medal? <a href=\"http://www.quora.com/Olympic-Games/What-is-it-like-to-be-an-Olympic-athlete-after-winning-or-not-winning-the-Olympics\">This Quora post</a> from Peter Cipollone, rowing gold medallist in 2004, goes some way to answering the question. </p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We did not even need to be on the lists for parties. We skipped the line and flashed our medals at the door. Huge entourage wants to come in, too? No problem. Feel like jumping up on the stage with the band? Do it! Stage dive the crowd? That's cool, too. Global sponsors called to ask if we might attend a breakfast and answer a few questions for a fat honorarium. With pleasure. We were just getting back from a party somewhere and breakfast with people genuinely excited about the Olympics sounded fun. Everywhere we went, it was a celebration. People on the street would stop us and ask if their children could see the medal. That was the best.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012bbc895cb5fcda7f9522a\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Equestrian cross-country</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Back in Greenwich the Olympic Broadcasting Authority are setting up some of the 45 cameras which will capture the equestrian cross-country event. One of their technical types wasn't sure whether the camera he was setting up near one of the 28 obstacles would spook the horses, so he flagged down someone who looked like he knew about these things. Inevitably, it was our own Stephen Moss. They decided, with the further assistance of a helpful group of German grooms, that the camera would be fine.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b9a495cb5fcda7f95229\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Controversial German tweet a 'cowardly fake'</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>A controversial Twitter message mocking Greek athletes, which appeared to have been written by a German hockey player, was actually a \"cowardly fake\", according to Germany's national Olympic committee. The tweet, attributed to the German Olympic flagbearer Natascha Keller, read: \"The Olympic village is filled with barefoot Greek athletes. As soon as we see them we are afraid that they will ask us for loans.\" More details <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-tweet-greeks-cowardly-fake\">here</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b91ab579c24ed04374d4\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Elsewhere in London...</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Away from the Olympic Park, Paolo Nutini, Duran Duran, Stereophonics and Snow Patrol play in the Opening Ceremony Celebration Concert in Hyde Park, so here's Simon Le Bon talking about the Olympics. \"The running events are incredible,\" he says.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qT3g5riyQp4\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/qT3g5riyQp4?wmode=opaque&fs=1&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b7bc95cb5fcda7f95227\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Opening ceremony sells out</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Guardian's Owen Gibson has tweeted the news organisers were so desperate to tell &ndash; it's a sell-out.<br /><br /></p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/owen_g/status/228875722368892929\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Locog confirms that all of the tickets for the opening ceremony are now sold out - even the eye wateringly expensive ones at £2,012.</p>&mdash; Owen Gibson (@owen_g) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/owen_g/status/228875722368892929\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T15:33:19+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b31295cb5fcda7f95224\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">More from the Olympic Park</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Guardian's Peter Walker is also at the scene.<br /><br /></p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I've just spent a while wandering through the Olympic park and, just before the first punters are allowed in ahead of the opening ceremony, the mood is very excitable, like that in a theatre before the biggest first night ever. The food stalls and programme kiosks are fully stocked and ready to go, and streams of performers are making their way across the vast open spaces to begin getting ready.<br /><br />Everyone seems in high sprits. One group of ceremony performers broke into a spontaneous chant of \"Sue Barker! Sue Barker!\" as the BBC presenter sailed past sedately in one of the small motorised buggies used to transport the infirm or important. She waved, almost regally, with a grin.<br /><br />The place seems full of groups of school-age children being shepherded about. I didn't see quite so many take part in the dress rehearals I witnessed, so maybe some are just getting a tour. But expect to see lots of young faces tonight, as the ceremony pushes that legacy thing.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b22e95cb5fcda7f95221\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Update from the Olympic Park</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Guardian's Sam Jones at the Olympic Park, where tonight's audience are starting to arrive in numbers.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>The crowds making their way from a heaving Statford station, through the Westfield shopping centre and into the park ahead of the opening ceremony are a beautifully international lot. The flags of Great Britain, the US, Honduras, Spain, China, Romania, Germany and the Dominican republic are tied around a fair few proud necks. The crowds are moving smoothly once they get through the bottleneck of the shopping centre and begin the waiting til the gates open at 5pm. Dawn Schier, her husband Peter and their daughter and son in law have come up from Essex and are resplendent in union flag T-shirts and olympic-hooped sunglasses.<br /><br />\"I'm 67 and this is only going to happen once, so why not?\" said Dawn. Their already high spirits have been further raised by a pair of celebrity knight sightings: Sir Cliff Richard and Sir Steve Redgrave. How do they feel about  the prospect of a couple of hours of queuing? \"We might still be here tomorrow,\" said Dawn with a smile. \"But who cares? We're just getting into the spirit.\"</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b0e5b579c24ed04374cf\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Iran's Olympians</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Elsewhere on The Guardian, Saeed Kamali Dehghan has written <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/iran-blog/2012/jul/27/iran-london-2012-olympic-games\">this interesting piece about Iran's Olympians</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012b088b579c24ed04374ce\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Sudanese athlete seeks asylum</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/27/sports/olympics/olympic-runner-from-sudan-seeks-asylum-in-london.html?_r=1\">According to the New York Times</a>, a Sudanese Olympic athlete is seeking political asylum in the UK. Sudan has sent only six athletes to the Olympics, but the identity of the athlete involved has not been disclosed.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012ad3cb579c24ed04374cd\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Weightlifting favourite withdraws</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Russian gold medal favourite Oksana Slivenko has been forced to withdraw from the weightlifting competition at the London Olympic Games, reports the Press Association. The world and European champion, a silver medallist in Beijing four years ago, is understood to have suffered an injury in training this week and will not now compete in the women's 69kg category. Slivenko's spot in Russia's weightlifting squad has been taken by Natalya Zabolotnaya, who will compete in the women's 75kg weight category.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012aafb95cb5fcda7f9521f\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Michelle Obama v Spongebob Squarepants</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The question: who's better at penalty-taking, <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MPbJLG65iMg\">Diana Ross</a> or Michelle Obama? The answer: there's not much in it, but it's the first lady.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/video/2012/jul/27/london-olympics-michelle-obama-video\"                        data-show-ads=\"true\"                                data-video-name=\"London 2012 Olympics: Michelle Obama takes a football penalty - video\"                                > <object width=\"460\" height=\"307\"><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"opaque\"></param><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/video/2012/jul/27/london-olympics-michelle-obama-video/json\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"460\" height=\"307\" flashvars=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/video/2012/jul/27/london-olympics-michelle-obama-video/json\" wmode=\"opaque\"></embed></object> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012a9e9b579c24ed04374cb\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Munich 1972 remembered</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Unlikely to get a mention in the opening ceremony tonight, despite <a href=\"http://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/story/2012-07-26/munich-israeli-widows-silent-protest-opening-ceremony/56494020/1\">an appeal by some victims' families</a>, are the Israeli athletes and coaches killed in the Black September terrorist attack 40 years ago in 1972, so thanks to Gary Naylor for reminding me not to make the same mistake here. A small ceremony was held at the Israeli embassy this morning, while <a href=\"http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/70539/silences-held-despite-iocs-refusal-mark-munich-opening-ceremony\">the Jewish Chronicle reports</a> that around 200 people held a minute's silence in Trafalgar Square. A further ceremony will be held on 6 August, away from the Olympics. Jacques Rogge, the IOC president, <a href=\"http://edition.cnn.com/2012/07/22/sport/olympics-munich-silence/index.html\">said on Saturday</a> that \"the Opening Ceremony is an atmosphere that is not fit to remember such a tragic incident\", but has not been forthcoming with an alternative, more fitting moment during the Olympics themselves.</p> <p>I would encourage you to read <a href=\"http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1086527/index.htm\">this piece, published in 1972, by the American marathon runner Kenny Moore</a>. I wrote about the incident for The Guardian's 50 Stunning Olympic Moments series in May. You can read that article <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/blog/2012/may/02/50-stunning-olympic-moments-munich-72\">here</a>.</p> <p>EDIT: I have been forwarded <a href=\"http://www.timesofisrael.com/ankie-spitzers-40-year-old-quest-for-justice-from-the-ioc/\">this article about Ankie Spitzer</a>, widow of the 1972 fencing coach Andrei Spitzer, who has been leading the families' campaign for commemoration, which also seems worth a read.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012a669b579c24ed04374ca\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Opening ceremony</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>American Olympic fans are miffed because they will be unable to watch the opening ceremony live, as Matt Wells explains.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>NBC, which reportedly paid $1.18bn for rights to the London Olympics, is not broadcasting or streaming the opening ceremony live. Instead, it is saving it for prime time, showing the whole thing some four hours later, with coverage starting at 7.30pm on the east coast. It's even being delayed for viewers on the west coast, who will have to wait until 7.30pm Pacific time before it's shown on their local affiliates. The reason  of course is money - NBC wants to maximise its more valuable primetime audience. </p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012a5f4b579c24ed04374c9\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery – women's results</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The results of this afternoon's women's team and individual ranking rounds are in. South Koreans occupy the top two positions in <a href=\"http://www.london2012.com/archery/event/women-individual/phase=arw070900/index.html\">the individual rankings</a> (the top Briton, Naomi Folkard, came 42nd). Korea also unsurprisingly hold the top position in <a href=\"http://www.london2012.com/archery/event/women-team/phase=arw470900/index.html\">the team rankings</a>, ahead of the US. Great Britain came 11th out of 12, ahead of Ukraine. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012a46795cb5fcda7f9521e\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Equestrianism: wellies get the boot</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Good news for fans going to watch the equestrian events at Greenwich: a week ago organisers said that ticketholders would need to wear wellies, but now they've been told to put them away again. Now we're told that a sturdy pair of shoes should see you right, unless this weekend is particularly wet. As Stephen Moss points out, \"all this only applies to Monday's cross-country. You can access the arena, where everything else takes place, without walking on a blade of grass.\"</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012a312b579c24ed04374c6\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Was an Olympic record set today?</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Guardian US have developed this <a href=\"http://wasanolympicrecordsettoday.com\">Olympic record tracker</a>. There have already been two. (Or so we're told; they weren't on television or held in front of spectators. I'll believe them.)</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012a265b579c24ed04374c5\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Inside the athletes' village</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>For those who want to know what an athlete's bedroom looks like, here's American modern pentathlete Margaux Isaksen's. She likes her quilt.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/MargauxIsaksen/status/228848415419817984\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>My room in the village. I wonder if I can keep the comforter??! So cool. And pentathlon took up 2 patches on the quilt! <a href=\"http://t.co/LQmun6fL\" title=\"http://twitter.com/MargauxIsaksen/status/228848415419817984/photo/1\">twitter.com/MargauxIsaksen…</a></p>&mdash; Margaux Isaksen (@MargauxIsaksen) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MargauxIsaksen/status/228848415419817984\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T13:44:49+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50129e9b95cb5fcda7f9521b\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Olympic Park redevelopment</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here are <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/interactive/2012/jul/27/olympic-regeneration-legacy-stratford\">some before and after photographs of the Olympic park</a>, rather smartly presented. Just slide the central bar left and right to reveal more of either photo.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50129cfa95cb5fcda7f95219\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Equestrian cross-country course unveiling</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Guardian's Stephen Moss is in Greenwich today, where they are gearing up for the start of the equestrian events, and has filed this report.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>The cross-country course at Greenwich is about to be unveiled to the media &ndash; the riders walked it for the first time yesterday &ndash; and I&rsquo;ve just been handed a detailed description, with comments by designer Sue Benson. It will start with what she calls a &ldquo;friendly hedge, framed in a diamond, in recognition of the queen&rsquo;s jubilee&rdquo;. It&rsquo;s called the Diamond Jubilee Hedge, and on Monday will launch the eventers on their 10-minute journey over 28 oddly shaped obstacles.<br /><br />Obstacle six, called the Planet and inspired by the nearby Greenwich Observatory, is particularly bizarre, and it will be intriguing to see how the riders orbit it. If they get past that, their next obstacle will be a crescent moon. Benson holds out great hope for this fence, saying &ldquo;the photographic opportunities will put equestrian sports on the map forever&rdquo;. &ldquo;Jumping into space requires a leap of faith,&rdquo; she adds, &ldquo;but Olympic competitors are used to this.&rdquo; With a backdrop of the Queen&rsquo;s House and Canary Wharf across the river, this could be the picture that Locog will say justifies the &pound;60m-plus spent building the temporary equestrian facilities at Greenwich.<br /><br />Further down the course, riders will encounter the River Bank, Saxon Village, Ancient Market Place, East End Barrows, and the Tower of London &ndash; Danny Boyle is not the only one making the Olympics an excuse to reflect on British history. There&rsquo;s a fence in honour of Greenwich, another called the Altar whose meaning is not entirely clear, a homage to cricket with a fence featuring bats and stumps, and best of all from my point of view as a chess nut a fence called the Chess Table with a chessboard and huge hand-made pieces. Naturally, the knights are prominent. The course ends with the Olympic Horses &ndash; two horses made of recycled horseshoes, framing a giant horseshoe. The riders have to jump through the horseshoe. The course is strange, elegant, eccentric and should be fun both to ride and decode.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50129baf95cb5fcda7f95216\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Hockey</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Team GB&rsquo;s women hockey players are in peak form, according to goalkeeper Beth Storry, 34, a former bronze medalist at the European Championships, the World Cup and the Commonwealth Games.<br /><br />From not qualifying for the Athens 2004 Olympics, to ranking ninth at Beijing 2008, the team are now considered fourth best in the world and Storry told Press Association Sport the players &ldquo;really believe that we can beat all the teams out there.&rdquo;</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501297efb579c24ed04374b8\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Laura Robson gets tennis place</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Laura Robson, who had been loitering nervously at the gates of the Olympic village as first alternative, has been handed an Olympic spot after the withdrawal of Croatia's Petra Martic, and will play Czech Lucie Safarova in the first round on Sunday. If she wins that, she could play Maria Sharapova in round two. Robson plays her first Olympic match tomorrow evening in the women's doubles with Watson, the pair taking on fifth seeds Angelique Kerber and Sabine Lisicki from Germany on Court 12.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012934095cb5fcda7f95206\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Liverpool mayor in Twitter &quot;error&quot;</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>News of a minor Twitter storm involving the mayor of Liverpool, Joe Anderson. Earlier today he tweeted <a href=\"https://p.twimg.com/Ayz-UY8CYAEOYLX.jpg\">this message</a>, which has since been deleted and replaced with this: </p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/joeforliverpool/status/228827644567904256\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Apologies for the previous tweet re: Olympics. The comments were posted in error without the Mayor's authority and don't reflect his views</p>&mdash; Joe Anderson (@joeforliverpool) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/joeforliverpool/status/228827644567904256\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T12:22:16+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501291d4b579c24ed04374b0\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Today's best Olympic pictures</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The day's best pictures are being lovingly curated in one place. And that place is <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/olympics-2012-pictures\">here</a>. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50128f0895cb5fcda7f95205\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Ticket collection hell</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>You may have <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/24/olympics-2012-ticket-fiasco\">read earlier this week</a> about the lengthy queues at the offices of Cosport, who sold Olympic tickets to the residents of America, Australia and on behalf of a few European countries. Though they have provided a bit more shade and water to the waiting hordes since people had to wait upwards of seven hours when their doors first opened on Monday, the queue hasn't gone away. Here's the scene right now, with newcomers told they will be there for at least three hours.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Josh_Landy/status/228833467679506432\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Knew one of these Olympic ticket pick ups would be a nightmare. Estimated queue 3 hours. CoSport = absurd. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search/%25232012tweeps\">#2012tweeps</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/pDsqjMq2\" title=\"http://twitter.com/Josh_Landy/status/228833467679506432/photo/1\">twitter.com/Josh_Landy/sta…</a></p>&mdash; Josh Landy (@Josh_Landy) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Josh_Landy/status/228833467679506432\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T12:45:25+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50128ce6b579c24ed04374ab\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Actual live sport!</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The women's team and individual archery ranking rounds are under way. The men's ranking rounds <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50127d05b579c24ed0437496\">took place this morning</a>. As reported earlier, this is the only event of the Olympics which takes place behind closed doors, with no spectators or television cameras present. Results as we get them.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50128aacb579c24ed04374a7\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">#Romneyshambles latest</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Olympic legend Carl Lewis has spoken about <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/jul/26/mitt-romney-olympics-blunder?intcmp=239\">Mitt Romney's Olympic gaffe</a>. \"Seriously, some Americans just shouldn't leave the country,\" he said. \"Of course London is ready.\" Read more, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/jul/27/carl-lewis-mitt-romney-olympics\">here</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50128782b579c24ed04374a5\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Handing over the torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>That's it from me for today. My colleague <strong>Simon Burnton</strong> will be taking over for the afternoon, and <strong>Xan Brooks</strong> will be your guide for the evening. Thanks for all the comments, tweets, and emails about what time the opening ceremony starts. Enjoy ...</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50128737b579c24ed04374a4\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Pork scratchings</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>CNN has <a href=\"http://www.cnngo.com/explorations/life/how-be-london-local-10-tips-faking-it-970492%20\">produced a <strong>guide to American</strong>s about how to survive in London</a>.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>The secret to blending in with locals lies solely in the use of one word: &ldquo;innit&rdquo; - a colloquial abbreviation of &ldquo;isn&rsquo;t it?&rdquo; Confusingly, although &ldquo;innit&rdquo; implies a query, this uniquely London method of punctuating sentences is a purely rhetorical device. Thus, &ldquo;time for drink, innit?&rdquo; is wrong, but &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve had four pints and no dinner, innit&rdquo; is grammatically perfect.</p> </blockquote> <p>The guide adds: \"In some bars you may see something called 'Pork Scratchings' for sale. These are not for you.\"</p> <p>Shaun Ryder once came into a pub I was working in in Manchester. He lost 10p in the pub's phone box and came up to the bar to complain. \"Just give me a packet of pork scratchings and we'll call it quits,\" he suggested amicably. I did.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501285e7b579c24ed04374a3\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Taxi</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Taxi drivers</strong> in London have brought forward their protest over their exclusion from Olympic lanes <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/uk/2012/jul/27/london-taxi-protest-olympic-lanes\">after police imposed restrictions</a>. It will now take place at 2pm instead of 5pm.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501283d9b579c24ed043749d\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Here is a summary of today’s key events so far</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>&bull; <strong>The Olympic torch has <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50127a55b579c24ed0437494\">travelled down the Thames in a rowbarge to City Hall</a> as London prepares for tonight&rsquo;s opening ceremony of the 2012 Olympic Games.</strong> The ceremony starts at 9pm BST, and according to London Olympics chief Lord Coe will be watched by four billion people around the globe. <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-19000273\">Here&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;ve seen of it so far</a>. Bells were rung all over the country at the same time this morning to mark the start of the Games in an artwork by Martin Creed. <br /><br />&bull; <strong>Mitt Romney&rsquo;s tactless &ldquo;Romneyshambles&rdquo; comments about the London Games continue to draw comment.</strong> <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-501278b0b579c24ed043748d%20\">Former Olympic sprinter Carl Lewis said</a>: &ldquo;Stay home if you don't know what to say.&rdquo; Jeremy Hunt, the culture secretary, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50125dc895cb1d4f92af22c6\">said he was more interested in what Jacques Rogge, the president of the International Olympic Committee, thought</a>, and anyway Britain invented more sports than America did, so there. Reports that his dad is bigger than Romney&rsquo;s dad cannot be confirmed at time of going to press.  <br /><br />&bull; <strong>South Korea have claimed the first two world records of London 2012 in the men's archery ranking round.</strong> Im Dong-hyun, who is registered blind, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-501269aab579025f1313e4a8\">broke his own individual record</a> for 72 arrows and joined Kim Bubmin and Oh Jin-hyek to set a new team mark for 216 arrows. Meanwhile the South Korean<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/sailing\"> Sailing</a> Federation has<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-south-korean-sailing\"> apologised on behalf of the coach Lee Jae-cheol after he was sent home from London 2012 for drink driving</a>. There was anger and confusion outside Lord&rsquo;s, where the archery took place, because the event was advertised as &ldquo;unticketed&rdquo; &ndash; meaning not open to the public rather than free, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50125ac4b579025f1313e49b%20\">as many disappointed archery fans had assumed</a>. <br /><br />&bull; <strong>Usain Bolt, the expected sprint superstar of this Olympics, has spoken about his rivalry with Yohan Blake, his training partner who stunned him by beating him in the 100m and 200m Jamaican Olympic trials.</strong> After the 200m, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50127814b579c24ed043748c\">Bolt told him</a>: &ldquo;This is never going to happen again.&rdquo; Bolt said he was disgusted with his performance in that race he couldn&rsquo;t watch it again. <br /><br />&bull; <strong>Mark Cavendish <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-5012718bb579025f1313e4ac\">has described</a> the British cycling squad as &ldquo;the dream team&rdquo;, and said he feels no additional pressure despite potentially being the first home champion of London 2012 in tomorrow&rsquo;s road race.</strong><br /><br /><strong>&bull; Basketball&rsquo;s Dan Clark and Mike Lenzly have been passed fit to play for Great Britain in the Olympics after <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50125bacb579025f1313e49c\">recovering from injuries suffered last week</a>.</strong><br /><br />&bull; <strong>China&rsquo;s top diplomat have told the London 2012 overdogs to behave in a &ldquo;<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50126051b579025f1313e49e%20\">modest and unassuming</a>&rdquo; way at the Games.</strong><br /><br />&bull; <strong>Boris Johnson, the mayor of London, defended the Olympic organisers for allowing McDonald&rsquo;s to be a sponsor, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-50126cf8b579025f1313e4aa%20\">saying criticism of the fast food giant was &ldquo;just bourgeois snobbery&rdquo;</a> and McDonald&rsquo;s food was &ldquo;nutritious, delicious [and] extremely good for you &hellip; not that I eat a lot of it myself&rdquo;. </strong><br /><br /><strong>&bull; <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog#block-501275ecb579025f1313e4b1\">Hunt nearly hit somebody with a bell</a>. </strong></p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50128505b579c24ed04374a0\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Police</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Police have now left a branch of Sainsbury's by Wandsworth Bridge where they had been called as the Olympic torch passed along that stretch of the Thames, writes <strong>Hilary Aked</strong>. Crowds out to see the flame had earlier witnessed what one resident called a \"huge\" police presence.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127f42b579c24ed043749a\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Scheduling</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>People are still emailing me to ask what time the opening ceremony starts. It starts at <strong>9pm BST</strong>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127d81b579c24ed0437498\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The <strong>Gloriana</strong> is moving off back down the Thames now. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127d05b579c24ed0437496\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>South Korea</strong> took the top three seedings this morning in the archery ranking rounds. Great Britain's Larry Godfrey, who recorded a personal best of 680, was seeded fourth.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127c7a95cb5fcda7f951ed\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Clegg</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Nick Clegg has given 14 people - a &ldquo;small but very impressive group&rdquo; including community activists and military personnel - tickets for tonight&rsquo;s <strong>Olympic opening ceremony</strong>, <strong>Hilary Aked</strong> reports.<br /><br />Shabaz Ferozdin, a 35-year-old youth manager from Reading, who met the deputy prime minister at a youth centre in Peckham, south London, is one of the small group being offered what Clegg called a &ldquo;once in a lifetime opportunity to enjoy the greatest show on earth&rdquo;.<br /><br />Kate Allatt, 42, a charity campaigner and locked-in syndrome sufferer from Dore in Sheffield, David Johnston, 30, CEO of the Social Mobility Foundation, three men involved in military action in Libya with RAF Waddington, and Derek and Gill Towler, 65 and 61, who set up a community centre in Croydon to support displaced residents during last summer&rsquo;s riots, are also on the list.<br /><br />Clegg said: &ldquo;Every day I meet inspirational people who give their all to good causes and for the benefit of others. I rarely get a chance to show them how grateful I am, how grateful we all are, for their dedication and selflessness.&rdquo;</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127c2a95cb5fcda7f951eb\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Drinking game</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10151062788247313&amp;set=a.10150136200032313.299679.323973322312&amp;type=1&amp;theater\">An Olympic ceremony drinking game is doing the rounds on Facebook</a> &ndash; that's the <strong>Olympic spirit</strong> in a nutshell. You have to drink five fingers when \"a country's uniform is so bad they look embarrassed\", and five when \"an innuendo about the bell is made\". An innuendo about the bell? Not on the BBC, I hope. <br /><br /></p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127b9495cb5fcda7f951ea\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Pun-dit</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Great <strong>David Brent moment</strong> just now on BBC News.</p> <p>Andy Hunt, Team GB's chef de mission, was told the athletes would take over tomorrow after today's day of pageantry and fun. He replied:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>The rubber, excuse the pun, the rubber hits the road tomorrow ... you know, with the road cycling race ... </p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127a55b579c24ed0437494\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Torch relay</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here's the barge that brought the <strong>Olympic flame</strong> down the Thames to City Hall today. You can see the torch-bearer with the flame standing in front of the Olympic rings.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-5db5076a-7211-428f-a0cc-5791f85ee4f6\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343388188117/-460.png\" alt=\"The Olympic flame by City Hall in London on 27 July 2012.\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>The Olympic flame by City Hall in London today. Screengrab: Sky News</figcaption> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501279a2b579c24ed0437491\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The <strong>Olympic flame</strong> is now being transferred from the cauldron on the boat to one of the torches, and has now been carried on to the pontoon displaying the Olympic rings. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501278b0b579c24ed043748d\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Carl on Mitt</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Carl Lewis</strong> has given his view on Mitt Romney's controversial London Olympic comments. <a href=\"http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/romneyshambles--some-americans-just-shouldnt-leave-the-country-says-carl-lewis-7981698.html\">It's a great quote</a>:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I swear, sometimes I think some Americans shouldn't leave the country. Are you kidding me, stay home if you don't know what to say.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127814b579c24ed043748c\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Athletics</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Usain Bolt</strong> was interviewed by Colin Jackson yesterday in <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Px3qAyxh2k\">a Google Hangout</a>, writes <strong>Paul Campbell</strong>.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>If the pressure of being the poster boy for London 2012 is playing on the sprinter's mind, he hides it well. Bolt chatted openly with Jackson and fans from across the world about developing a love of sport by watching cricket with his dad. </p> <p>His sprinting talent was noticed by his cricket coach, who encouraged him to run by offering to buy Bolt's lunch.</p> <p>Although he is now more of a football fan, Bolt would like to see Twenty20 introduced for future Olympics. </p> <p>Bolt was keen to talk about his early career, especially winning the 2002 World Junior Championships in Jamaica, which he rates as his most memorable achievement: \"That's one of the greatest moments for me. People say Beijing, but it's not. It was being at home and I've never been so nervous in my entire life. I won and that was a moment that defined my whole life. I cannot forget that moment. It was so much fun - so much awesome.\"</p> <p>Turning to the present day, Bolt gives an insight to his rivalry with Yohan Blake, his training partner. After <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lNm6ZUuQTvk\">Blake won the 200m in the Olympic trials</a>, Bolt warned him: \"This is never going to happen again.\"</p> <p>\"I said that to him as I work so hard on my 200m and, when I watched the replay of that race, I was so disgusted I could not watch it again. My technique and years of practice went out the window in that race. It was really bad for me and really sad. But I got past that, I'm back on full form, I'm all right and ready to go.\"</p> </blockquote>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Px3qAyxh2k\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/5Px3qAyxh2k?wmode=opaque&fs=1&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501276f2b579c24ed043748b\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Badminton</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Last-minute rescheduling will see world silver medallists Imogen Bankier and Chris Adcock open Team GB's badminton campaign early tomorrow morning as they take on Russians Alexandr Nikolaenko and Valeri Sorokina at 9.40am, writes <strong>Hilary Aked</strong>.<br /><br />Later on their British teammate Susan Egelstaff will start her medal bid playing Slovenia&rsquo;s Maja Tvrdy at 12.30pm at Wembley Arena while another GB hopeful, Rajiv Ouseph, will face Henri Hurskainen of Sweden in his opening game at 8.15pm on Sunday evening.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012767f95cb5fcda7f951e5\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Gloriana</strong> is pulling alongside a special pontoon displaying the Olympic rings. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127615b579025f1313e4b2\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>There's a large crowd outside <strong>City Hall</strong> as the torch approaches on the boat Gloriana. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501275ecb579025f1313e4b1\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bell</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here's a video of <strong>Jeremy Hunt</strong> almost hitting somebody with a bell.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/jeremy-hunt-olympic-bell-video\"                        data-show-ads=\"true\"                                data-video-name=\"Jeremy Hunt almost hits woman with Olympic bell end - video\"                                > <object width=\"460\" height=\"307\"><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"opaque\"></param><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/jeremy-hunt-olympic-bell-video/json\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"460\" height=\"307\" flashvars=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/jeremy-hunt-olympic-bell-video/json\" wmode=\"opaque\"></embed></object> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501275a995cb1d4f92af22ce\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Olympic torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Olympic torch is reaching the end of its <strong>journey down the Thames</strong>. It's just passing HMS Belfast near Tower Bridge and City Hall. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50127523b579025f1313e4b0\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bell-ringing</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Jeremy Hunt</strong>, the culture secretary, tried to ring a bell earlier on the banks of the Thames. Unfortunately <a href=\"http://makeagif.com/i/8SkOtU\">the bell flew off the handle and into some passers-by</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012747eb579025f1313e4af\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Sailing</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The <strong>South Korean</strong> <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/sailing\">Sailing</a> Federation has <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-south-korean-sailing\">apologised on behalf of the coach Lee Jae-cheol after he was sent home from London 2012 for drink driving</a>.</p> <p>The Federation said Lee was pulled over by police after attending a banquet hosted by the mayor of Weymouth which is staging the sailing regatta:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Coach Lee Jae-cheol attended a banquet and drank wine and beer on 25 July. It is true that Lee, who can't drink well, was caught drunk driving by the police when he was returning alone to the athletes' village at 5am for training after sleeping for some time to get sober at the federation's own place outside the village.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012736cb579025f1313e4ae\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Police</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>There is a police incident at the Sainsbury&rsquo;s on Townmead Road by <strong>Wandsworth Bridge</strong>, which the Olympic torch has just passed beneath. The Metropolitan police confirmed that officers were currently on the scene investigating but would not give further details at this point.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012718bb579025f1313e4ac\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Cycling</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Mark Cavendish</strong> has described the British cycling squad as &ldquo;the dream team&rdquo;, but said he feels no additional pressure despite potentially being the first home champion of London 2012 in tomorrow&rsquo;s road race.<br /><br />Cavendish said:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>An Olympic medal, regardless if it's the first or last on offer, it's an Olympic medal for your team. It's easy to get emotional about it. I've been nervous this week. We've trained to be able to deal with those nerves and we've got to put it to bed. We've got a process which we have to adhere to. It's a process we know if we commit 100% we've got the best chance of winning.</p> </blockquote> <p>Cavendish is joined in the five-man squad by Tour de France winner Bradley Wiggins, Chris Froome, who was second in le Tour, David Millar and Ian Stannard. Cavendish said:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We were motoring along in training and I just looked round and it's the dream team. We've got first and second on GC [general classification] of the Tour de France, four guys who won stages of the Tour de France [Wiggins, Froome, Millar and himself] and a British champion [Stannard], all guys incredibly motivated, incredibly patriotic and incredibly loyal to each other. If we wanted to win this bike race we couldn't be in a better situation team-wise.</p> </blockquote> <p>His post-Olympics plans illustrate the packed schedules of top cyclists: &ldquo;I'm racing on Sunday in Belgium, Monday in Pau, Tuesday in Holland. It's my day job. That's what professional cycling is. It's entertainment.\"</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-ada95822-ae54-4de3-902d-dce50e5a0659\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343386337105/a6fff2c7-2b5d-49a4-96f0-728458642972-460.jpeg\" alt=\"Mark Cavendish of Team GB. Photograph: Bryn Lennon/Getty Images\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Mark Cavendish of Team GB. Photograph: Bryn Lennon/Getty Images</figcaption> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50126f0795cb1d4f92af22cb\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Gymnastics</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>British gymnast <strong>Louis Smith</strong>, who will compete in a qualification event tomorrow in the North Greenwich Arena, has said his team will play it safe at this early stage to ensure they finish in the top eight in order to qualify, reports <strong>Hilary Aked</strong>. The pommel horse specialist said:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>The things that will be running through my head when I step up to compete are: 'I'm ready, I've got my nan looking over me, I've got the support of my friends and family in the crowd. I've been waiting 19 years for this,' so it is just going to be all positive thoughts running through my head.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50126e5c95cb1d4f92af22ca\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Olympic torch</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here's <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/olympic-torch-hampton-court-video\">the Olympic torch on the start of its <strong>journey down the Thames</strong> today</a>.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/olympic-torch-hampton-court-video\"                        data-show-ads=\"true\"                                data-video-name=\"London 2012: Olympic torch begins final journey - video\"                                > <object width=\"460\" height=\"307\"><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"opaque\"></param><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/olympic-torch-hampton-court-video/json\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"460\" height=\"307\" flashvars=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/olympic-torch-hampton-court-video/json\" wmode=\"opaque\"></embed></object> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50126cf8b579025f1313e4aa\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bursting with nutrients</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Boris Johnson</strong> has apologised for his tube travel chaos warning adverts, <a href=\"http://london2012.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/07/26/boris-being-boris-londons-mayor-goes-to-bat-for-mcdonalds-sort-of/\">according to the New York Times</a>. The mayor told the foreign media:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>I apologise to everybody who has been irritated by my Tannoy announcements. They are, I have to admit, very irritating but the reason for doing them is that they attract attention.</p> </blockquote> <p>He also hit back at critics of the Olympic organisers for allowing McDonald&rsquo;s to be a sponsor.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>This is all just bourgeois snobbery about McDonald&rsquo;s. It&rsquo;s classic liberal hysteria about very nutritious, delicious food &mdash; extremely good for you, I&rsquo;m told &mdash; not that I eat a lot of it myself. Apparently this stuff is absolutely bursting with nutrients.</p> </blockquote> <p>A shame Boris is missing out on all those nutrients, really.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50126aa095cb1d4f92af22c9\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Sorry, I forgot to add that <strong>Im Dong-hyun</strong>, who just broke that archery record, is legally blind. I know. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501269aab579025f1313e4a8\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>You can't watch today's archery <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog?commentpage=last#block-50125ac4b579025f1313e49b\">in person</a> or <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog?commentpage=last#block-5012469595cb1d4f92af22bb\">on TV</a>, but apparently <strong>South Korea</strong> have claimed the first two world records of London 2012 in the men's ranking round.</p> <p>Im Dong-hyun broke his own individual record for 72 arrows and joined Kim Bubmin and Oh Jin-hyek to set a new team mark for 216 arrows.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501268cab579025f1313e4a7\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Transport</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>My colleague <strong>Hilary Aked</strong> sends a travel update. Things are looking pretty good.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>Pudding Mill Lane station next to the Olympic park is closed but there are no major underground problems at present except minor delays on the Jubilee line.<br /><br />On the roads, park and ride sites close to the M25 either side of the Dartford Crossing are said to be &ldquo;a major pinch point&rdquo; with clockwise traffic moving at 10mph and tailbacks of up to ten miles. Expect 30 minute delays in the other direction. TfL are advising of congestion on the following routes: A3, A40, A12, A13 and A2.<br /><br />Taxi drivers will also be protesting today about being excluded from Olympic traffic lanes - which came into effect Wednesday but will be more heavily employed from today - at Hyde Park Corner. Previous demonstrations brought traffic to a standstill. The Blackwall tunnel northbound has just been reopened following a cement spillage.</p> </blockquote> <p>On Twitter, Jon Morgan reports that rebellion is building against mayor of London Boris Johnson's cheery tube warnings:</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Morganised/status/228742878443208704\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Tube platform announcer just cut off Boris recording with a \"Yeah, thanks Boris.\" Huge cheer all along the platform.</p>&mdash; Jon Morgan (@Morganised) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Morganised/status/228742878443208704\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T06:45:26+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50126612b579025f1313e4a5\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Adverts</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>I know I'm falling into their trap. But this <strong>unofficial Olympic advert</strong> for Specsavers is very good.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/TaylorHerringPR/status/228759828422615040\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>good work Specsavers <a href=\"http://t.co/Nw9ZQKpx\" title=\"http://twitter.com/chariscroft/status/228749621495750656/photo/1\">twitter.com/chariscroft/st…</a> (via @<a href=\"https://twitter.com/chariscroft\">chariscroft</a>)</p>&mdash; James Herring (@TaylorHerringPR) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TaylorHerringPR/status/228759828422615040\" data-datetime=\"2012-07-27T07:52:47+00:00\">July 27, 2012</a></blockquote> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012652bb579025f1313e4a3\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bells</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here's <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/audio/2012/jul/27/bell-ringers-olympic-opening\">Charlotte Higgins's audio</a> of Martin Creed's <strong>All the Bells</strong> this morning.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012640fb579025f1313e4a2\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Blur songs</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog?commentpage=last#block-50124fb4b579025f1313e498\">David Cameron says</a> he wants the Olympics to demonstrate both sides of Britain: beefeaters and <strong>Blur</strong>.<br /><br />Here are the top 10 most appropriate Blur songs for the Olympics:<br /><br />1. Advert<br />2. Best Days<br />3. Coffee and TV<br />4. Entertain Me<br />5. London Loves<br />6. Avoid the Traffic<br />7. On your Own<br />8. She&rsquo;s so High<br />9. The Great Escape<br />10. To the End<br /><br />And here are the top 5 least appropriate:<br /><br />1. Slow Down<br />2. This is a Low<br />3. No Distance Left to Run<br />4. Out of Time<br />5. It Could be You</p> <p>Let's have a listen to London Loves. </p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rRMKB9WUars\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/rRMKB9WUars?wmode=opaque&fs=1&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50126051b579025f1313e49e\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">China</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>While the UK and US <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog?commentpage=last#block-50125dc895cb1d4f92af22c6\">collapse into fratricidal feuding</a>, the country that will probably walk away with the biggest haul of gold medals this year has advised its athletes to behave in a &ldquo;<strong>modest and unassuming</strong>&rdquo; way in London. What instruction could more effectively bespeak China&rsquo;s top-dog status? <br /><br />In 2008, the Beijing hosts won 51 golds to the US&rsquo;s 36, Russia&rsquo;s 23 and Britain&rsquo;s 19. The US won 110 medals in total, to China&rsquo;s 100. <br /><br />Dai Binggou, China&rsquo;s top diplomat, said:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>We are still a developing country and should keep a modest and prudent attitude even though China is becoming more and more globally influential. We are considered a big sporting country but we are still not a sporting giant. There are still gaps between China and global sports giants in many aspects. We must be modest and unassuming in learning from other countries and continue to raise our athletic abilities.</p> </blockquote> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50125e8db579025f1313e49d\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">TV listings</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>A number of people have emailed me to ask what time the opening ceremony is starting tonight. The answer is <strong>9pm</strong>. <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/tv/guide\">BBC1's coverage begins at 7pm</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50125dc895cb1d4f92af22c6\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Hunting</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-2012-olympics-live-blog?commentpage=last#block-50124c5895cb1d4f92af22bf%20\">Like Boris Johnson</a>,<strong> Jeremy Hunt,</strong> the culture secretary, got in a dig at Mitt Romney over the US presidential contender&rsquo;s comments that there were \"disconcerting\" signs around the London Games and it was \"hard to know just how well it will turn out\".</p> <p>But whereas Boris geed up a Hyde Park crowd with some broad-brush rabble-rousing, Hunt chose to creep to the president of the IOC a little bit, following that up with some slightly unstatesmanlike jingoism:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>The person I care about more is Jacques Rogge, the president of the International Olympic Committee, who said London was the best prepared city he had ever seen. When we have the opening ceremony tonight and we tell the world that eight of the world's top 10 sports were either invented or codified in Britain - and only two in America - I hope Mr Romney is watching.</p> </blockquote> <p>Hunt also said worries about queues at Heathrow were &ldquo;the dog that didn&rsquo;t bark&rdquo; &ndash; &rdquo;Heathrow's gone incredibly smoothly.&rdquo;</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50125bacb579025f1313e49c\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Basketball</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Dan Clark</strong> and <strong>Mike Lenzly</strong> have been passed fit to play for Great Britain in the Olympics after recovering from injuries suffered last week.</p> <p>Lenzly tore a calf muscle in last Thursday's friendly against the United States, while Clark suffered an ankle sprain playing against Tunisia at the weekend. Today was the deadline for Britain to make a change if one or both of the players were ruled out.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50125b2395cb1d4f92af22c4\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Helpline</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p data-component=\"comp : r2 : Article : standfirst_cta\">Post your last-minute questions and answer each other's Olympic worries in our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/27/london-olympics-helpine-answer-readers-questions\">London 2012 Olympics helpline open thread</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50125ac4b579025f1313e49b\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The BBC is reporting <strong>anger and confusion</strong> outside Lord's, where the archery ranking rounds are going on &ndash; contests to decide athletes' placings for the initial rounds. </p> <p>The event has been advertised as \"unticketed\"; what the London organising committee meant by that was that the event was closed to spectators.</p> <p>But a lot of hopeful archery fans &ndash; and ticketing websites &ndash; thought it meant \"free\" and have turned up. They are not pleased. </p> <p>Locog says it has not advertised tickets for today's archery events. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501256f0b579025f1313e49a\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Blink and you'll miss it</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here's a <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c3VbCdtJClo\">very, very brief collection of snippets</a> from <strong>rehearsals</strong> for the opening and closing ceremonies.<br /><br /></p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c3VbCdtJClo\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/c3VbCdtJClo?wmode=opaque&fs=1&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012564395cb1d4f92af22c2\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bells</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>My colleague <strong>Charlotte Higgins</strong> has just been to the leafy streets of Kentish Town to ring in the Olympics &ndash; or, rather, participate in Martin Creed's <a href=\"http://www.allthebells.com/\">Work No. 1197, All The Bells In A Country Rung As Quickly And Loudly As Possible For Three Minutes</a>.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>At five to eight, it looked like it was going to be just me, a Games Maker volunteer from Devon and Chinese state TV (the journalist was called Tingting Ai) but then a motley and quite respectably large crowd of children, grown-ups, folk on bikes, some blokes who looked like they were decorators and several dogs turned up, with sleigh bells, ships' bells, the local primary school bell, temple bells, bike bells, and, in the case of the local organiser, Sandy Nairne, director of the National Portrait Gallery, what he referred to as &ldquo;the spare cat bell&rdquo;.</p> <p>The result was deafening - my ears are still ringing - and extremely good-natured, aside from the woman staring furiously from an upper window who I suspect had received rather a rude awakening.</p> </blockquote> <p>We'll have an audio recording of all that up soon.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501251b7b579025f1313e499\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Underwear</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>A top Olympic official has said lawyers worried about ambush marketing undermining Games sponsors <strong>will not instigate checks on players' underwear prior to games</strong>, the Press Association reports.</p> <p>It would be impractical, said Denis Oswald, a senior member of the International Olympic Committee.</p> <p>And people say the Olympic organisers are power-crazed control freaks with no sense of proportion. They're not &ndash; they're completely reasonable. They know as well as you do that it would be impractical to check every athlete's underwear, no matter how much they might want to.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012504095cb1d4f92af22c0\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Stadium</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here are some <strong>Olympic volunteers</strong> arriving at the stadium this morning.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-85c33e3b-2d05-46f9-b3db-e9a7610ef143\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343376878170/Volunteers-arrive-at-the--006.jpg\" alt=\"Volunteers arrive at the Olympic park, as final preparations take place\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Photograph: Martin Rickett/PA</figcaption> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50124fb4b579025f1313e498\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Cameron</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Britain is ready to welcome \"the greatest show on earth\", <strong>David Cameron</strong> said this morning. The prime minister told reporters in Downing Street the country must show the world \"the best of Britain\" over the next two weeks. </p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>It's very exciting ... I think it's a great opportunity to show the world the best of Britain, a country that's got an incredibly rich past but actually a very exciting and vibrant future. Somebody asked me yesterday what face of Britain I wanted to put forward, Blur or the beefeaters, and frankly it's both.  We have got a great past, a very exciting future and this is a great moment for our country, so we must seize it.</p> </blockquote>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-247c3698-e7bf-4c28-b674-01cd98e95483\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343377308847/-460.png\" alt=\"David Cameron on the day of the Olympic opening ceremony, 27 July 2012.\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>David Cameron on the day of the Olympic opening ceremony, 27 July 2012. Screengrab: BBC News</figcaption> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50124c5895cb1d4f92af22bf\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Boris</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/boris-johnson-mitt-romney-olympics-video\">Here's Boris Johnson using <strong>Mitt Romney</strong>'s negative comments</a> about the Games to rev up the crowd at Hyde Park yesterday.</p> <p>It's not unthinkable that Boris could be PM and Mitt US president by the time of the next Olympics, so they might have to learn to get on a bit better. This is what Boris told the crowd:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>There are some people who are coming from around the world who don't yet know about all the preparations we've done to get London ready in the last seven years. I hear there's a guy called Mitt Romney who wants to know whether we're ready. He wants to know whether we're ready. Are we ready? Are we ready? Yes, we are!</p> <p>The venues are ready, the stadium is ready, the aquatics centre is ready, the velodrome is ready, the security is ready, the police are ready, the transport system is ready [don't push it, Boris]. And our Team GB athletes are ready, aren't they! Team GB is ready! They're going to win more gold, silver, and bronze medals than you'd need to bail out Greece and Spain together!</p> </blockquote> <p>Always good to counter one diplomatic row by casually kicking off another ...</p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/boris-johnson-mitt-romney-olympics-video\"                        data-show-ads=\"true\"                                data-video-name=\"Boris Johnson mocks Mitt Romney over London 2012 Olympics comments - video\"                                > <object width=\"460\" height=\"307\"><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"opaque\"></param><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/boris-johnson-mitt-romney-olympics-video/json\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/video/embed\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"460\" height=\"307\" flashvars=\"endpoint=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/video/2012/jul/27/boris-johnson-mitt-romney-olympics-video/json\" wmode=\"opaque\"></embed></object> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501248f0b579025f1313e497\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Major</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>John Major was just interviewed on BBC Radio 4's Today programme. He said that if people see Usain Bolt run an astonishing time in the 100m at this Olympics, that will be something they put in their \"<strong>memory box</strong>\" forever.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012480095cb1d4f92af22bd\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Weather</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Here&rsquo;s a quick <strong>London weather forecast</strong> for today, <a href=\"http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/public/weather/forecast/?tab=map&amp;map=SignificantWeather&amp;locId=352409&amp;zoom=7\">courtesy of the Met Office</a>. It&rsquo;s a greyer, cooler morning than we&rsquo;ve been enjoying over the last few days. It is due to start raining at around 10am, until about 4pm, after which we'll see a slightly cloudy afternoon and a high of 23 &ndash; leaving the skies above the opening ceremony free of rain this evening. Fingers crossed.</p> <p>Tomorrow will be sunny with a high of 21, Sunday will be rainy with a high of 18, Monday will be cloudy with a high of 19, and Tuesday will be rainy with a high of 19. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012469595cb1d4f92af22bb\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Archery</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>I just spoke to the <strong>BBC </strong>about where you can watch today's archery ranking rounds. Bad news. You can't watch it anywhere. The Olympic Broadcasting Services aren't screening it, the BBC said. Roger Mosey, the BBC's director of London 2012, said earlier this week: \"The most exciting thing for us this time is that you will have every single venue live from first thing in the morning to last thing at night.\" The BBC press office told me today's archery would be the only exception to this. </p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-c9c14faa-58b5-4680-832c-b3625beb189b\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/7/27/1343374966908/4206d9e1-48c3-484e-8231-e49fde0aee85-460.jpeg\" alt=\"Naomi Folkard of Great Britain during archery practice at Lord's on 25 July 2012. Photograph: Paul Gilham/Getty Images\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Naomi Folkard of Great Britain during archery practice at Lord's on 25 July 2012. Photograph: Paul Gilham/Getty Images</figcaption> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501244cc95cb1d4f92af22b9\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Swimming</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The US Olympic swim team were the only people in the world not to have produced a lip-sync version of Carly Rae Jepson's<strong> Call Me Maybe</strong>. Until now.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-qU3kwef-yo\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/-qU3kwef-yo?wmode=opaque&fs=1&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012427295cb1d4f92af22b7\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Opening ceremony</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Everyone involved with the opening ceremony has maintained throughout that they are not attempting to compete with <strong>Beijing</strong>'s in 2008, a stunning display of synchronisation complete with a <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2008/aug/12/olympics2008.china1%20\">fake child singer </a>and <a href=\"http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/olympics/2534499/Beijing-Olympic-2008-opening-ceremony-giant-firework-footprints-faked.html\">CGI-enhanced fireworks</a>. The moment where the final torch-bearer flies into the sky and runs around the top of the stadium is still jaw-dropping. And look out for 14-year-old Tom Daley with the British delegation, introduced by the American commentator as \"a young diver\". </p>  <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JsDY1Ha83M8\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/JsDY1Ha83M8?wmode=opaque&fs=1&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure>  <p>Probably the most upsetting opening ceremony in recent memory was Seoul 1988, when many of the doves of peace released before the lighting of the Olympic flame were instantly <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xgAXCAWQUic\">incinerated</a> when it was lit.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501240d8b579025f1313e496\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>    <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Johnson has seen the rushes of the opening ceremony. It was a brilliant. People are going to cry hot tears when they see it, he says.</p> <p>Asked about Mitt Romney's negative comments yesterday, Johnson says the US presidential candidate has now been fulsome (sic) in his praise of the Olympics. It's good to have his support, the mayor says.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012405c95cb1d4f92af22b6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>    <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>This is our chance to show the world what we're about and throw a real party, Boris says. He wants to see a great economic benefit from the Games. </p> <p>\"If you talk to these tycoons,\" Boris says, they don't need any persuading that the UK is a great city to invest in. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-5012401cb579025f1313e495\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Boris</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p><strong>Boris Johnson</strong>, the mayor of London, is being interviewed on Radio 4's Today programme.</p> <p>Anthropologists are going to look back and ask why people were so enthusiastic about the torch relay. \"Hard-bitten members of my family\" loved it, Johnson says. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50123fe2b579025f1313e494\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">Bells</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>Martin Creed's All the Bells is now taking place across the country. Starting with Big Ben, people are ringing bells around the country. </p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-50123cd0b579025f1313e493\" class=\"block is-key-event\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>   <h2 class=\"block-title\">From the Guardian</h2>  <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>The Guardian is full to the brim with Olympic stories this morning. <strong>Here are some of the highlights</strong>:<br /><br />&bull; These Olympic weeks will offer answers to a clutch of questions that have nagged at us since the last time London hosted the Games in 1948, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/27/london-2012-time-to-find-out-who-we-are\">writes Jonathan Freedland</a>. What exactly is our place in the world? How do we compare to other countries and to the country we used to be? What kind of nation are we anyway?<br /><br />&bull; Usain Bolt has admitted for the first time that he has been suffered from a slight injury, but claims he is now fully recovered and ready to &ldquo;become a legend&rdquo;, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-olympics-usain-bolt\">Owen Gibson reports</a>.  Bolt was greeted with whoops and yelps from his fellow athletes, who seemed to recognise him as first among equals, when he turned up for a leisurely lunch at the athletes&rsquo; village yesterday, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-usain-bolt-olympic-canteen\">writes Robert Booth</a>. <br /><br />&bull; The Games may actually be David Cameron&rsquo;s economic strategy, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-economic-strategy%20\">muses Marina Hyde</a>.</p> <p>&bull; Kings, queens and presidents will get the chance to experience a bit of British queuing tonight, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/jul/26/diplomatic-niceties-world-leaders\">reports Julian Borger</a>, as they line up outside Buckingham Palace to travel from the Queen&rsquo;s reception to the Olympic Stadium. &ldquo;It will be first come, first served, and if you do not recognise &ndash; or are officially at war with &ndash; the country whose potentate you end up alongside, that will be too bad.&rdquo; <br /><br />&bull; No 10 was stunned by what my American colleagues are calling the &ldquo;Romneyshambles&rdquo; yesterday, when the US presidential candidate Mitt Romney, visiting London, made some negative and cautious comments about how the Games might turn out. Boris Johnson <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/jul/26/mitt-romney-olympics-blunder\">responded at last night&rsquo;s Olympic concert at Hyde Park</a>: \"I hear there's a guy called Mitt Romney who wants to know whether we're ready,\" the mayor yelled from the stage to a cheering crowd. \"He wants to know whether we're ready. Are we ready? Are we ready? Yes, we are.\"<br /><br />&bull; Barney Ronay <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2012/jul/26/great-britain-senegal-olympic-football\">marvels at the creation of the Team GB men&rsquo;s football team</a>.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>British amateur teams competed regularly at the Olympics until the Munich Games, but these are the first real, actual professional players to appear under the union flag. They will also probably be the last, so great are the assorted tensions in the wings of Team GB, chiefly the fear of loss of influence within football's governing body Fifa. Which is a shame as in the hours before kick-off Manchester seemed surprisingly hospitable to this footballing flag of convenience, the streets of the Piccadilly area thronging with newbie fans and the procession towards Old Trafford producing an eclectic pageant of mingled union flag-ishness, reminiscent of a high-Britpop music video or an extended Benny Hill credits sequence.</p> </blockquote> <p>&bull; And <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-team-gb-senegal\">here is Andy Hunter&rsquo;s match GB v Senegal report</a>. Brazil v Egypt is <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/brazil-egypt-football-london-2012\">here</a>. Spain v Japan is <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-spain-japan-football-report%20\">here</a>. <br /><br />&bull; <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2012/jul/26/danny-boyle-olympic-ceremony-director%20\">Steve Rose profiles Danny Boyle</a>, the director of tonight&rsquo;s opening ceremony. <br /><br />&bull; <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-murray-wawrinka-tennis%20\">Kevin Mitchell looks at</a> Andy Murray&rsquo;s possible route to the Olympic tennis final (if that isn&rsquo;t jinxing things too much), where he might face his Wimbledon nemesis Roger Federer. <br /><br />&bull; Anna Meares cuts a contrasting figure to her great rival Victoria Pendleton but acknowledges their battles have been good for cycling, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/london-2012-anna-meares-victoria-pendleton\">writes William Fotheringham</a>. <br /><br />&bull; &ldquo;Confidence feels like it's a weapon. You're in control,&rdquo; <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/mo-farah-london-2012-olympics%20\">British middle-distance runner Mo Farah tells Anna Kessel</a>.</p> <p>&bull; Charismatic American swimmer Ryan Lochte may win the popularity contest at London 2012, but will he be crowned greatest all-round swimmer, <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/blog/2012/jul/26/ryan-lochte-michael-phelps-olympic\">asks Andy Bull</a>. <br /><br />&bull; The 2014 Winter Olympics torch relay <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/jul/26/winter-olympic-torch-space-2014?newsfeed=true\">will include a trip into space</a>, the Russians say. That's cool.<br /><br />&bull; And here&rsquo;s Steve Bell&rsquo;s take on the Games. I didn&rsquo;t think Wenlock and Mandeville could look any more terrifying than they already do. <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/cartoon/2012/jul/26/london-2012-cameron-osborne-cartoon\">But I was wrong</a>.</p> </div>   </div> <div id=\"block-501231b7b579025f1313e492\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2012-09-03T14:38:14.369+01:00\">2.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">BST</span></time> </p>    <div class=\"block-elements\">  <p>This is it.<br /><br />Tonight at 9pm Danny Boyle&rsquo;s eagerly-awaited &pound;27m Olympic <strong>opening ceremony</strong> will officially kick off the 2012 London Games at the Olympic Stadium in Stratford.</p> <p>Seven years of preparation end tonight &ndash; and tomorrow the Olympic Games begin. <br /><br />Almost unbelievably in this era of Twitter and Facebook, the tens of thousands of people who watched rehearsals for the opening ceremony this week have largely kept the details secret, although some aspects of the show have been announced already &ndash; including the choice of Sir Paul McCartney to bring the curtain down &ndash; and photos have shown the stadium transformed into a giant mock-up of the English countryside, complete with live farm animals, cricket players and actors in Victorian dress, with the curve of the Thames sweeping through the arena. Daniel Craig's James Bond is also said to feature.</p> <p>Short video footage of rehearsals for the opening ceremony was <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-19000273\">shown on the BBC yesterday</a>. Scenes showing what appeared to be people with illuminated wings riding bicycles were broadcast under an agreement that allowed a 30-second clip to be shown by rights holders including the BBC 24 hours before the ceremony started.<br /><br />Today&rsquo;s events started off at around 6.55am when the <strong>Olympic torch</strong> began to make its stately way down the Thames on Gloriana, the Queen&rsquo;s rowbarge that featured in her jubilee flotilla, from Hampton Court Palace in south-west London to City Hall beside Tower Bridge, where it is due to arrive at around 12.55pm. The torch will then set off from City Hall to Stratford at 9pm and is due to appear at the Olympic Stadium at 11pm. It is still not known who will light the flame in the stadium, signalling the start of the Games, although bookmaker William Hill suspended betting yesterday on Roger Bannister, the first man to run a four-minute mile, after a run of big bets. <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/jul/26/olympic-opening-ceremony-flame\">Guardian readers have made their suggestions here</a>.<br /><br />And at 8.12am, open a window and see if you can hear Martin Creed&rsquo;s national artwork <a href=\"http://www.allthebells.com/\"><strong>All the Bells</strong></a>, which involves as many people as possible around the country ringing bells as loud as they can at the same time.<br /><br />The Olympic <strong>football</strong> tournament has already begun &ndash; with Great Britain's women starting in style with a 1-0 victory and the men's team drawing 1-1 in a bruising game against Senegal last night &ndash; and the <strong>archery</strong> gets going today, with men&rsquo;s and women&rsquo;s individual ranking rounds at Lord&rsquo;s at 9am and the team ranking rounds at 1pm.</p> <p>We'll have live coverage of all today's Olympic events here throughout the day, and tonight my colleague <strong>Xan Brooks</stron